<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167134928870">
<term>closed system</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167131586266">system for which the mass is constant and the net external force on the system is zero</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167134540321">
<term>Law of Conservation of Momentum</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167134540326">total momentum of a closed system cannot change</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167131257470">
<term>system</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167131586212">object or collection of objects whose motion is currently under investigation; however, your system is defined at the start of the problem, you must keep that definition for the entire problem</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
